[2] Cholera - India (Andaman and Nicobar Islands Union Territory)
Date: Wed, 11 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Hindu [edited]
<http://www.hindu.com/thehindu/holnus/001200610110314.htm>

The Andaman and Nicobar administration on Tue 10 Oct 2006 claimed that
there was no reason to panic about a cholera epidemic in the islands. "No
fresh case has been reported from any part of the islands except for 8
cases in children, admitted to a local hospital earlier and were cured,"
according to islands' health director N Sadasivan. He said only 3 to 4
cases of suspected cholera had been treated in the children's ward of G B
Pant Hospital.
Earlier, a team of doctors from the Health Department and Indian Centre for
Medical Research had moved to all the areas from where 8 suspected cholera
cases were reported.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[The Andaman and Nicobar Islands Union Territory is an administrative
division of India. Unlike states, which have their own local governments,
union territories are ruled directly by the national government. There are
over 570 islands in the territory, of which only some 38 are permanently
inhabited. A map showing the location of the Indian territory in the Bay of
Bengal can be found at:
<http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/andamanandnicobar/andaman-nicobar-island.gif>.
- Mod.LL]
