[3] Undiagnosed illness, human, fatal - Indonesia (West Java)
Date: Sat 7 Oct 2006
From: Theresa <theresa42@gmail.com>
Source: Pikiran Rakyat [edited]
<http://www.pikiran-rakyat.com/cetak/2006/102006/07/0103.htm>

As of Fri, 6 Oct 2006, 238 people were ill and 5 dead from an illness
producing diarrhea and vomiting. According to the Garut Regent, Agus
Supriadi, who was accompanied by Kabag public relations and Garut Regional
Government representatives, 124 patients are still being treated in DPT
Limbangan Community Health Center.
The regent believes these cases may be related to the source of water and
is seeking an alternative large clean source for the community. While
waiting for construction of an artesian well in Cibiuk, the regent
continued, the Garut Regional Government will increase assistance and
supplies of clean water there.
Construction on the artesian well in Cibiuk could begin within a month, the
regent reported. There is a commitment to supply extra help to the Darul
Ulm Islamic School in the Jatisari Village, Kec Karangpawitan.
Results could be expected from the laboratory on several samples as early
as Mon or Tue [8-9 Oct 2006] said Dr Hendi Buniman, who is with the
sanitation department. He said that _E. coli_ was suspected but that his
investigators did yet want to confirm it as the cause.
Dr Hendi believes part of the problem may be environmental sanitation. He
reported that only 43 per cent of the households in Garut have a family
toilet. There is also concern about sanitation in the home. Many people in
the area still defecate in the river and in gardens, from where food is
consumed. He said that the diarrhea illness and vomiting was in north Garut
territory, especially Kec, Malangbong, Cibatu, and Sukawening.
A similar situation may have happened in 1993 in Malangbong and the
surrounding area.
--
Theresa
<theresa42@gmail.com>
[The area sanitation seems lacking. Perhaps this is _E. coli_ or
Salmonella. There is no indication of whether these are water or fecal
samples or both. We hope, however, that there will be some word from the
laboratory. - Mod.TG
A map of Indonesia showing West Java (Jawa Barat) on the western side of
the island of Java can be found at:
<http://www.exportinfo.org/worldfactbook/maps/indonesia_map.gif>. - Mod.LL]
