[4] Cholera - Uganda (Amuru)
Date: Tue, 10 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Monitor (Kampala) [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200610091515.html>

A fresh cholera outbreak has been reported in the newly created Amuru
district bordering South Sudan and Adjumani district. Three people were
reportedly admitted at Bibia Health Centre in Atiak Sub-county.
The acting district director of health services, Dr Erisa Mulwani,
confirmed the outbreak. He urged local leaders to sensitize the community
on maintaining hygiene in their homes to avoid catching cholera.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[This posting infers that Amuru has been now made into its own district.
Amuru had been one of the 23 sub-counties of Gulu. Amuru means "boiling"
because of a hot spring located in the area. A map of Uganda can be found
at: <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/uganda.pdf>. The area
where Amuru is located is close to Sudan and Adjumani. - Mod.LL]
******
[5] Cholera - Angola (Benguela)
Date: Mon, 9 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=478741>

Around 24 people, among them 7 children under the age of 5, died of cholera
from 4 to 7 Oct 2006 in the commune of Tumbulo, Cubal municipality in the
southwestern Benguela Province, ANGOP has learned from sanitary authorities.
According to the head of the health sector in Cubal, Benjamim Ndambuka,
from the 65 cases notified in the commune of Tumbulo, 42 were assisted in
the local hospital and 2 resulted in death while the rest 22 died at home.
To control the outbreak of the epidemics, according to the source, a group
of health technicians are already working in the locality.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing the location of the province of Benguela and the
city of Cubal can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf> - Mod.LL]
