[6] Cholera - Angola (Cunene)
Date: Fri, 13 Oct 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=479938>

Of the 49 recorded cases, 7 people died from cholera in Kahama
municipality, southern Cunene Province, from 31 Sep to 10 Oct 2006, ANGOP
learnt from the Health provincial director, David Eduardo Haiumba.
According to the government official, of the people who caught the illness
only 15 were admitted to hospital.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing the location of the province of Cunene can be
found at: <http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>
With this report, it is still not clear if 2 provinces (Moxico and Lunda
Sul) have been affected. - Mod.LL]
